-- Europe shares fall after report of Russia convoy attack
-- By Tricia Wright
-- Fri Aug 15, 2014 11:01AM EDT
-- None



LONDON, Aug 15 (Reuters) - European shares turned negative on Friday afternoon, with traders citing a report that Ukraine troops had attacked and destroyed part of a Russian armed convoy.

A Ukraine military spokesman said Ukrainian forces had engaged and partially destroyed part of the convoy. [ID:nL6N0QL1IB]